    "The minimization of the bound in Theorem 2.1 leads to the Gibbs posterior ρλ that will put mass on all the Θ j in general, so this is a model aggregation procedure in the spirit of McAllester (1999).",
    "On the other hand, we can also restrict the minimization in the PAC-Bayes bound to distributions that would charge only one of the models, that is, to ρ ∈ P(Θ 1) ∪ • • • ∪ P(Θ M).",
    "Theorem 2.1 becomes:",
    "Thus, we can propose the following procedure:",
    "• first, we build the Gibbs posterior for each model j,"
